From: agentOS Runtime <runtime@agentos.invalid>
Subject: [PATCH] brush-builtins: use bash block units for ulimit

Bash defines the `ulimit -c` and `ulimit -f` block unit as 1024 bytes. Brush
grouped `Block` with its separate `HalfKBytes` unit and therefore installed
limits at half the requested value. This caused every truncate around an exact
RLIMIT_FSIZE boundary to receive SIGXFSZ. Keep the pipe-size half-kilobyte unit
at 512 bytes and use 1024 bytes for Bash block limits.

diff --git a/src/ulimit.rs b/src/ulimit.rs
--- a/src/ulimit.rs
+++ b/src/ulimit.rs
@@ -24,7 +24,7 @@ impl Unit {
     const fn scale(self) -> u64 {
         match self {
-            Self::Block | Self::HalfKBytes => 512,
-            Self::KBytes => 1024,
+            Self::Block | Self::KBytes => 1024,
+            Self::HalfKBytes => 512,
             _ => 1,
         }
     }
